casebody.data:
Friday, February 28, 1997

MOTION DOCKET

96-2247. State ex rel. The Plain Dealer v. Ohio Dept. of Ins.

In Mandamus. This cause originated in this court on the filing of a complaint for a writ of mandamus.

Upon consideration of relators’ and intervening respondent’s motions for protective orders,

IT IS ORDERED by the court that the motions for protective orders be, and hereby are, denied.

Moyer, C.J., Resnick and Lundberg Stratton, JJ., would grant relators’ motion only.
